# Malayalam Quiz Question Standards

Applies to every `*.json` question bank in this repo **except**:
- `english_language.json` — English only (synonyms, grammar, vocabulary)
- `current_affairs_manifest.json` — metadata, not questions

## JSON shape

Each question:

```json
{
  "id": "prefix_001",
  "question": "…",
  "options": ["…", "…", "…", "…"],
  "answer": "…",
  "difficulty": "easy | medium | hard"
}
```

Four distinct options; `answer` must exactly match one option.

## 1. Language — pure Malayalam

Write **question, all options, and answer** in Malayalam script. Kerala PSC / competitive-exam tone.

### English allowed only when necessary

Keep English (or Latin script) **only** for items with no standard Malayalam equivalent:

| Keep in English/Latin | Malayalam instead |
|-------------------------|-------------------|
| ODI, T20, IPL, ICC, FIFA, GST, ISRO, NASA, WHO | — |
| Duckworth-Lewis-Stern, Powerplay (with context) | — |
| Full-form questions: GST, NEP, IMF in stem/options | — |
| Proper nouns: London, Paris, Einstein | transliterate: ലണ്ടൻ, പാരീസ് |
| **Book / literary work titles** — see below | — |

### Book and literary work titles

Use each work’s title in **its own language** (the language it was written/published in):

| Work type | Title in question/options |
|-----------|---------------------------|
| Malayalam book | Malayalam: `'ഇരുപ്പ്'`, `'നാലുകെട്ട്'`, `'ഖാസാക്കിന്റെ ഇതിഹാസം'` |
| English book | English: `'The God of Small Things'`, `'Wuthering Heights'`, `'Discovery of India'` |
| Other languages | Original or standard title: `'Don Quixote'`, `'Les Misérables'` |

- Question stem stays Malayalam; only the **title** keeps its source language.
- Do **not** translate English book titles into Malayalam (or vice versa).
- All options in a title-matching question must follow the same rule (English with English, Malayalam with Malayalam).

```text
❌ 'ചെറിയ കാര്യങ്ങളുടെ ദൈവം' — English novel; keep English title
❌ 'Iruppu' — Malayalam work; use Malayalam script
✅ 'The God of Small Things' രചിച്ചത് ആരാണ്?
✅ 'നാലുകെട്ട്' രചിച്ചത് ആരാണ്?
✅ Which is written by Arundhati Roy? → options include The God of Small Things (in english_language.json only)
```

**Do not** leave descriptive English in Malayalam sentences:

```text
❌ 2022 FIFA World Cup-ന്റെ വിജയി?
❌ Which country hosted the Olympics?
❌ enthu / aaru / what is (Romanized or English stems)

✅ 2022-ലെ FIFA ലോകകപ്പ് വിജയിച്ചത് ഏത് രാജ്യം?
✅ ഒളിമ്പിക്സ് ആതിഥ്യം വഹിച്ച രാജ്യം ഏത്?
✅ Duckworth-Lewis-Stern രീതി എന്താണ്?
✅ ODI ഒരു ഇന്നിംഗ്സിലെ ഓവറുകൾ എത്ര?
```

Acronyms in options are fine when the question tests recognition (e.g. GST Council → options IMF, WHO, GST, WTO).

## 2. No Manglish

- No Romanized Malayalam (`enthu`, `evide`, `njan`).
- No English–Malayalam code-switching in one phrase (`match-ന്റെ`, `team-ൽ`).
- Translate the **sentence**; keep only the irreducible term (FIFA, ODI, etc.).
- Prefer established Malayalam terms: ലോകകപ്പ്, ആതിഥ്യം, വിജയി, നിയമസഭ, മുഖ്യമന്ത്രി.

## 3. Grammar and phrasing

- Use natural exam Malayalam: `ഏത്?`, `എവിടെ?`, `ആരാണ്?`, `എന്താണ്?`, `എത്ര?`
- Match subject–verb agreement; avoid calques from English word order.
- Use `-യുടെ` / `-ൽ` / `-ആണ്` correctly; prefer `-യുടെ` over glued English (`World Cup-ന്റെ` → `ലോകകപ്പിന്റെ`).
- Numbers: digits OK for years/counts (2022, 140); spell out in options when testing knowledge (`അഞ്ച്` vs `5` — be consistent within one question).
- Names: standard Malayalam spellings (കേരളം, തിരുവനന്തപുരം, ഇ.എം.എസ്. നമ്പൂതിരിപ്പാട്).

### Historical events — agent, patient, and verb

Bulk-generated or English-calqued questions often attach the **wrong subject** or **wrong verb** to an event. Before saving, identify:

| Role | Ask | Example (Pompeii / Vesuvius) |
|------|-----|------------------------------|
| **Agent** (cause) | What acted? | വെസൂവിയസ് അഗ്നിപർവതം |
| **Patient** (affected) | What changed? | പോംപെയ് നഗരം |
| **Verb** | What actually happened? | പൊട്ടിത്തെറിച്ച് … നശിച്ചു |

**Rules:**

1. **Patient gets the outcome** — destruction, fall, independence, annexation attach to the entity that changed, not the cause.
2. **Proper noun over generic label** — use Malayalam Wikipedia names (`വെസൂവിയസ് അഗ്നിപർവതം`), not vague words (`വുൽക്കാനോ`, `യുദ്ധം`, `വിപ്ലവം`) when a standard name exists.
3. **Verb must match the event type** — eruption → `പൊട്ടിത്തെറിച്ച്` / `സ്ഫോടനം`; earthquake → `ഉലച്ചു`; treaty → `ഒപ്പിട്ടു` / `ഉടമ്പടി`; battle → `നടന്നു` / `പരാജയപ്പെട്ടു`. Do not reuse `തകർന്നു` for every disaster.
4. **Read-aloud test** — if a Malayalam PSC aspirant would stumble or misread who did what, rewrite.

```text
❌ പോംപെയ് നഗരം വുൽക്കാനോ തകർന്ന വർഷം ഏത്?
   — volcano is subject but city was destroyed; generic വുൽക്കാനോ; തകർന്ന് wrong for eruption

✅ വെസൂവിയസ് അഗ്നിപർവതം പൊട്ടിത്തെറിച്ച് പോംപെയ് നഗരം നശിച്ച വർഷം ഏത്?
   — agent + correct verb + patient + outcome; names from ml.wikipedia
```

More patterns:

```text
❌ ബെർലിൻ മതിൽ വീണ വർഷം ഏത്?  → wall fell on its own (ambiguous)
✅ ബെർലിൻ മതിൽ ഇടിച്ചുമറിച്ച വർഷം ഏത്?

❌ ഹിരോഷിമയിൽ ആണ്ബോം വർഷിച്ച വുൽക്കാനോ …
✅ ഹിരോഷിമയിൽ ആണ്ബോം വർഷിച്ച വർഷം ഏത്?
```

## 4. Uniqueness and quality

Before adding or editing:

1. **Globally unique** — same `question` text must not appear in any other `*.json` file.
2. **Factually correct** — one unambiguous correct answer; distractors plausible but wrong.
3. **Non-trivial** — no duplicate concepts rephrased slightly; each question tests distinct knowledge.
4. **Balanced options** — similar length and format; avoid obvious wrong answers.
5. **ID discipline** — follow file prefix (`pok_`, `sca_`, `ca_2026_06_`, etc.); increment without gaps.

When bulk-editing, run `fill_unique.py` / `malayalamize_questions.py` patterns: malayalamize first, then verify no English leakage beyond allowed terms.

## 5. Research and verification — use the internet

**Always verify facts and Malayalam wording online** before adding or editing questions. Prefer Malayalam sources so spelling, terms, and phrasing match exam usage.

### Primary sources (use first)

| Source | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| [Malayalam Wikipedia](https://ml.wikipedia.org) | Facts, dates, names, places, Malayalam terminology |
| [സർവ്വവിജ്ഞാനകോശം / Sarvavijnanakosam](https://www.sarvavijnanakosam.in) | Authoritative Malayalam encyclopedia entries, Kerala & India topics |
| Other Malayalam references | Government portals (`.gov.in`, Kerala `.kerala.gov.in`), Kerala PSC syllabi, reputed Malayalam news sites |

### Secondary sources (when Malayalam entry is missing or thin)

- [English Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org) — cross-check facts only; **rewrite** the question in Malayalam using terms from Malayalam Wikipedia where they exist.
- Official org sites (ISRO, RBI, FIFA, etc.) for current data and scheme names.

### How to apply

1. Search the topic on **Malayalam Wikipedia** first; note standard Malayalam names and phrasing.
2. Cross-check dates, numbers, and spellings with a second source when possible.
3. Do **not** copy sentences verbatim — paraphrase into clear PSC-style Malayalam.
4. For book/author questions, confirm title language and spelling from Malayalam or original-language references.
5. For current affairs, prefer recent Malayalam news + official announcements over outdated entries.

```text
✅ ml.wikipedia.org → confirm person/place names and Malayalam terms before writing options
✅ Sarvavijnanakosam → confirm Kerala renaissance figure / work details
❌ Paste English Wikipedia sentence and translate word-for-word
❌ Guess dates or names without checking any source
```

## Quick review checklist

- [ ] Facts verified via Malayalam Wikipedia / Sarvavijnanakosam (or other reliable sources)
- [ ] Malayalam script throughout (except allowed terms and source-language book titles)
- [ ] Book/literary titles in their source language (English books in English, Malayalam in Malayalam)
- [ ] No Manglish or English sentence fragments
- [ ] Question unique across repo
- [ ] Four options, one correct answer, difficulty set
- [ ] Reads naturally to a Malayalam speaker preparing for Kerala PSC–style exams
- [ ] Historical questions: correct agent/patient, event-appropriate verb, proper noun from Malayalam Wikipedia (not generic calque)
